        "content": "<p>In semantics we currently tend to use definitions instead of classes, e.g.,</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"sd\">/-- An lts is image-finite if all images of its states are finite. -/</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">def</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">LTS</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">ImageFinite</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Prop</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"bp\">∀</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">s</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">μ</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Finite</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">lts</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">image</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">s</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">μ</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>There are many similar general properties for LTS and reduction systems, for example the diamond property and confluence.</p>\n<p>I wonder if these properties should be classes instead. Thoughts?</p>",
